{
  "name": "Carrot Cake Loaf",
  "description": "A plain-flour carrot loaf with no frosting, baked in a tin and sliced into 16. House calibration: the recipe's sugar-substitute is swapped for granulated Splenda, volume-matched to its sweetness (Splenda's small maltodextrin calories are counted); eggs are medium. The drizzle of olive oil is swapped for coconut oil.",
  "tags": [
    "carrot-cake",
    "cake",
    "protein",
    "baked",
    "bakeoff:carrot-base"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 16,
    "unit": "slices"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "b1",
        "order": 1,
        "section": "batter",
        "instructionText": "Whisk the wet ingredients (Greek yogurt, eggs, milk, oil, vanilla, Splenda) until smooth. Add the dry — flour, protein powder, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon — and stir JUST until no dry streaks remain. Don't overmix: the flour's gluten plus the protein powder turn an over-worked batter dense and rubbery. Fold in the grated carrot last, then pour into a lined loaf tin."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "b2",
        "order": 2,
        "section": "bake",
        "instructionText": "Bake at 350F (180C) until a skewer in the centre comes out clean and the middle is set (~200F internal) — about 40-50 min for a filled loaf tin; start checking at 35. Don't pull at 25 min, that's far too short for a loaf this deep. If the top colours before the centre sets, tent loosely with foil.",
        "temperature": 180
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "b3",
        "order": 3,
        "section": "cool",
        "instructionText": "Rest in the pan 10-15 min (it's fragile straight from the oven), then turn out onto a wire rack and cool COMPLETELY before slicing into 16. A warm protein loaf slices gummy and squashes; fully cooled it firms up and cuts clean. Even better the next day, wrapped at room temp. No frosting on this loaf — it's a plain spiced protein bake, sliced and eaten as-is to keep it lean; if you want extra, smear an individual slice with Splenda-sweetened 0% Greek yogurt (added at serving, so it stays off the recipe's macros)."
      }
    ],
